cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with Structure from Motion, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on averaging bifocal tensors (essential or fundamental matrices) in collinear camera settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper mentions autonomous car datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes algorithms for averaging, which involves optimization and spectral analysis, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with camera settings and geometric constraints, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
